review_blob: Batch001 - At 10.5% this is dangerously easy to drink. The sugar masks the strength well and the top notes are reminiscent of coca-cola. There is an undertone of bark that creeps in after the initial hit. A dead cert for anyone wanting to try something out of the ordinary.

Probably the winner for me from the first batch of beer from this new experimental brewery. Pours a nice hazy head with a citrusy aroma. Taste of tangerine jumps out, which may come from the sherry casks, and this is brought alive by the Brett, a lovely balance of sweet and sour. The texture is slighly syrupy, but with a nice fizz. Certainly looking forwards to the next batch.
beer_name: All Seeing Eye Cest La Lumire
